00:17:42.959 --> 00:17:46.760
and the gates of hell shall not prevail against it.

00:17:46.760 --> 00:17:49.360
Contextually within that wonderful promise,

00:17:49.360 --> 00:17:51.640
it was when Jesus came to His disciples

00:17:51.640 --> 00:17:53.320
and He asked this question.

00:17:53.320 --> 00:17:58.320
He says, whom do men say that I, the Son of Man, am?

00:17:59.100 --> 00:18:00.880
What a great question.

00:18:00.880 --> 00:18:02.360
Who do people say that I am?

00:18:03.179 --> 00:18:05.820
They answered and said, some say that thou art John the Baptist

00:18:05.820 --> 00:18:09.420
and some say that you're Elijah or Jeremiah

00:18:09.420 --> 00:18:11.580
or one of the prophets.

00:18:11.580 --> 00:18:14.860
We find that as this question is asked

00:18:14.860 --> 00:18:17.739
and He receives the response from the disciples

00:18:17.739 --> 00:18:21.059
as to whom men say that He is,

00:18:21.059 --> 00:18:24.779
then Jesus turns directly to them and says to them,

00:18:24.779 --> 00:18:28.820
but whom say ye that I am?

00:18:29.760 --> 00:18:31.040
Peter.

00:18:31.040 --> 00:18:33.840
He stands up with boldness and confidence

00:18:33.840 --> 00:18:37.960
and He says, thou art the Christ,

00:18:37.960 --> 00:18:40.679
the Son of the living God.

00:18:40.679 --> 00:18:43.559
Oh, what a powerful declaration of Peter.

00:18:43.559 --> 00:18:47.479
And we find that Peter receives the response from Jesus

00:18:47.479 --> 00:18:50.679
when he says, blessed art thou, Simon Barjona,

00:18:50.679 --> 00:18:53.599
for flesh and blood hath not revealed it unto thee,

00:18:53.599 --> 00:18:56.200
but my Father which is in heaven.

00:18:56.220 --> 00:18:59.619
And what a joy to understand that thou art the Christ,

00:18:59.619 --> 00:19:00.940
the Son of the living God.

00:19:00.940 --> 00:19:04.520
I'd ask you this morning, who do you say that Jesus is?

00:19:06.020 --> 00:19:08.780
Oh, we could go through our society today

00:19:08.780 --> 00:19:10.739
and we could ask many people,

00:19:10.739 --> 00:19:13.500
who do you say that Jesus is?

00:19:13.500 --> 00:19:15.799
Oh, you'd have some that would say He was a good man,

00:19:15.799 --> 00:19:18.900
He was a prophet, He was fill in the blank.

00:19:18.900 --> 00:19:20.940
I mean, all sorts of ideas,

00:19:20.940 --> 00:19:24.380
even within cults and false teachings

00:19:24.400 --> 00:19:27.479
that they have this idea of who Jesus is,

00:19:27.479 --> 00:19:30.359
but we find that Jesus is the Christ,

00:19:30.359 --> 00:19:32.440
He is the anointed one, He is Messiah,

00:19:32.440 --> 00:19:35.700
He is God in flesh.

00:19:35.700 --> 00:19:38.000
There's the Father that makes that known to us

00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:40.880
as we find here in this passage of Scripture.

00:19:40.880 --> 00:19:42.479
But I want you to notice

00:19:42.479 --> 00:19:45.640
that after Jesus has this interaction

00:19:45.640 --> 00:19:47.960
and He gets the question again,

00:19:47.960 --> 00:19:49.080
who is Jesus to you?

00:19:49.080 --> 00:19:52.520
I hope that you understand this morning that He is God.

00:19:52.539 --> 00:19:54.220
That He died for you.

00:19:54.220 --> 00:19:55.739
That He was buried in a borrowed tomb

00:19:55.739 --> 00:19:59.739
and He rose in victory even as we celebrate today

00:19:59.739 --> 00:20:01.739
conquering sin, death, and the grave.

00:20:01.739 --> 00:20:03.619
He is the Savior of the world,

00:20:03.619 --> 00:20:05.619
but He wants to be your Savior personally

00:20:05.619 --> 00:20:07.779
if you accept Him as your personal Savior.

00:20:07.779 --> 00:20:11.039
Understanding that your sin has a penalty.

00:20:11.039 --> 00:20:12.319
That penalty is death.

00:20:12.319 --> 00:20:14.779
Separation from God and the lake of fire forever.

00:20:14.779 --> 00:20:17.319
Oh, how terrible that is.

00:20:17.319 --> 00:20:18.659
But Jesus made a way. Why?

00:20:18.659 --> 00:20:20.819
Because He is the way.

00:20:20.819 --> 00:20:23.239
I am the way, the truth, and the life.

00:20:23.239 --> 00:20:26.779
And He made the way for you to be reconciled to God

00:20:26.779 --> 00:20:28.859
even as I preached last Sunday.

00:20:28.859 --> 00:20:29.979
Be reconciled to God.

00:20:29.979 --> 00:20:32.179
Oh, if you don't know the Lord Jesus Christ

00:20:32.179 --> 00:20:33.639
as your personal Savior today,

00:20:33.639 --> 00:20:35.899
if you do not have that 100% assurance

00:20:35.899 --> 00:20:37.219
that heaven is your home,

00:20:37.219 --> 00:20:39.939
would you trust Christ today?

00:20:39.939 --> 00:20:41.899
Would you understand who He is?

00:20:41.899 --> 00:20:43.419
Oh, He's not just a prophet.

00:20:43.419 --> 00:20:45.099
He's not just a good man.

00:20:45.099 --> 00:20:46.619
He's God.

00:20:46.619 --> 00:20:47.699
What a joy that is.

00:20:47.699 --> 00:20:51.059
But notice in v. 21 of Matthew 16,

00:20:51.059 --> 00:20:53.999
it says from that time forth

